# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored — never commit a populated one.
#
# Nothing here is required for `npm test` / `npm run build` / `npm run lint`: the local Hardhat
# network needs no secrets. These only matter for deploying and verifying against a live network.
#
# SECRETS: `DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY` and `ETHERSCAN_API_KEY` are read through Hardhat's
# `configVariable`, which checks the encrypted keystore FIRST and falls back to these env vars.
# So for anything holding real value, leave them blank here and use the keystore instead:
#
#     npx hardhat keystore set DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY
#     npx hardhat keystore set ETHERSCAN_API_KEY
#
# Both paths work identically from the scripts' point of view.

## RPC endpoint for the target network.
## Falls back to a public (rate-limited) Sepolia node when unset.
SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=

## Deployer key. TESTNET ONLY if you keep it here — see the keystore note above.
DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY=

## Block-explorer API key, used by `npx hardhat verify` / script/deploy/verifyAll.sh.
## Hardhat 3's verify task tries Etherscan, Blockscout and Sourcify.
ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=
